    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Describes the representation of monochrome continuous-tone digital images. Grayscale images differ from one-bit black and white images in that they are composed of levels of intensity in stages from black to white, not merely black or white.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000009221/Cotton and Oliver, Cyberspace Lexicon (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Beschrijft de weergave van digitale afbeeldingen met een monochroom tintverloop. Afbeeldingen met grijswaarden verschillen van 1-bits zwart-witte afbeeldingen omdat ze zijn opgebouwd met intensiteitsniveaus in fasen van zwart naar wit, niet enkel in zwart of wit.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>單色連續調之數位影像呈現。灰階影像與一位元黑白影像不同之處在於前者是由黑到白各階層的飽和度所組成，而非僅黑或白。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Descreve a representação de imagens digitais monocromáticas de tom contínuo. Imagens em tons de cinza diferem de imagens em preto e branco de um bit, pois são compostas de níveis de intensidade em estágios do preto ao branco, não apenas preto ou branco.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
